hoodMarket: Fenton is a 30-minute drive southwest from Saint Louis’ downtown and is bordered by the Meramec River to the north and Murphy to the south. Inventory is clustered in two areas: along Interstate 44 to the north, and more south near the Route 141 and Route 30 interchange. Blocks of space and the tenants filling them tend to be smaller relative to more dynamic industrial landscapes, as the vast majority of tenants serve the local population.,Proximity to interstates 44 and 270 provides access to logistics providers and manufacturers situated in the area. While most tenants do serve the local population, Fenton does allow for a more regional reach. For instance, while not directly located in Fenton, interstates 54 and 55 are a short drive and provide access to the points west and south. ,The new Fenton Logistics Park highlights recent development trends in the area. The lots that used to serve as a Chrysler Corporation assembly plant have been redeveloped, and will now house logistics tenants in nine new buildings. Tenants already occupying space in the park include CoreLink, Beckwood, Nexius and Hubbell. ,Fenton contains comparable asking rents with adjacent neighborhoods such as Hanley and West County. However, rent growth is slightly stronger in Fenton in recent months, the logical result of healthy leasing demand.

CRN offers 30’ - 32’ ceiling heights, 52’4”x50’ column spacing within and 52’4”x60’ at the loading dock areas, ESFR fire suppression, stunning office finishes and abundant tractor trailer parking and staging areas. propOverview:
Seaway Business Park is a 29 acre commercial office and warehouse complex located in Gulfport, Mississippi.  We offer office space for lease, office/warehouse space for lease and warehouse space for lease.  Some of our well known tenants include Sherwin Williams, Siemens, Primerica, Rotech Healthcare and AAA.  Our unique concept design allows for various types of businesses to operate in one professional setting with a quality unmatched in this area.
Seaway Business Park is located at 14231 Seaway Road in Gulfport, Mississippi with close and easy access to all of the major transportation arteries of the Mississippi Gulf Coast including Interstate 10, Highway 49, Highway 90 and Gulfport-Biloxi International Airport.  Gulfport is only one hour' s driving distance from New Orleans, Louisiana and Mobile, Alabama, providing an ideal location for a regional distribution center.  Seaway Business Park offers close proximity to major shopping centers, medical centers, restaurants and all area casinos.

propOverview:
2400 Hwy 45 N - Columbus, MS - near Hwy 82 - This property has a $300,000/year lease for 2 years with a 1 year option. They pay the proportionate share of taxes and insurance. Main property features include approx 328,000 SQUARE FOOT FACTORY/WAREHOUSE OFFICE SPACE SITUATED ON 30.20 ACRES. This Property is located in an area that is prime for manufacturing or retail development. Surrounding area includes all of the following - EXTREME HIGH DENSITY SHOPPING CENTER - MAJOR RETAILERS - NATIONAL FRANCHISE RESTAURANTS - NATIONAL HOTEL CHAINS - CAR DEALERSHIPS - THEATER. This is a PRIME RETAIL CORRIDOR. CURRENT LEASEBACK WITH STRONG TENANT FOR OFFICE AREA MAKES THIS A VERY DESIREABLE PROPERTY/INVESTMENT TO DEVELOP WITH CURRENT ESTABLISHED INCOME STREAM. This property presents an INCREDIBLE OPPORTUNITY for any MANUFACTURER seeking a new location or MAJOR RETAIL DEVELOPER.
PROPERTY FEATURES: 
•328,585 (approximately 299,000 warehouse, 30,000 office) total square feet industrial manufacturing facility on 30 acres in Columbus, MS. 
•LOCATION: The property is located in Lowndes County just off Routes 45 and 82, West of the Alabama border. 
•OFFICE FACILITIES: Approximately 30,000 sq. ft. of modern one-story office space; two conference rooms/training rooms to accommodate approximately 25 employees with wall mounted video screen and instructional board; raised floor climate controlled computer room and a fire rated walk-in vault; large break room. 
•MANUFACTURING AREA: First floor - vending type break room to accommodate approximately 30 employees. Second floor - manager’s office; training room to accommodate approximately 80 employees. 
•CONSTRUCTION: 6”-8” reinforced concrete floor with 12” concrete forklift curb, corrugated metal walls; wainscoting to 9’; 12” x 12” and 8” x 12” steel H columns spaced 30’ x 45’; 20’ x 80’; ceiling heights 25’ to eaves, 35’ to peak.
•TRUCK LOADING: North side: one 20’ x 26’ metal horizontal slide up drive-in door; one 16’ x 16’ metal roll up drive-in door; five 10’ x 10’ metal roll-up drive-in doors; one 16’ x 20’ metal roll-up drive-in doors. East side: one 8’ x 10’ dock-level roll-up door. South side: four 20’ x 26’ metal roll-up drive-in doors. West side: two 20’ x 25’ metal roll-up doors. 
•CRANES: Hook heights vary from 16’ – 20’; two 10-ton; eight 5-ton, twenty-nine 2-ton.
•SPRINKLER: Manufacturing building 30% sprinklered; office space 100% sprinklered; supply building 100% sprinklered. 
•UTILITIES: Power, water, and sewer served by Columbus Light and Water; gas served by Atmos. 
•HEAT: Heated by infrared and forced fan natural gas; 2,500 BTU ceiling suspended heaters. 
•LIGHTING: 400 watt mercury vapor, high pressure sodium metal halide.

propOverview:
We are pleased to offer you this ±35,375 SF Industrial Building!
This well kept manufacturing/warehouse facility is located on E Pythian near the intersection of Chestnut Expressway and
Glenstone. This location offers great access to Hwy 65, Division, and Glenstone.
Building features ±6,300 SF of office space. The ground floor office space is ±3,150 SF and features multiple private
offices, a meeting room, a break aera, and 2 restrooms. The second floor space office space is also ±3,150 SF and features
a full working kitchen, 2 restrooms.
The warehouse/manufacturing space has 2 grade level doors and 3 standard height dock doors. Grade level doors range
between 12'-14' tall. The warehouse/manufacturing space is also equipped with men's & women's multi-stall restrooms,
electrical drop downs, and a sprinkler system as well as 3 ac units.
Building lies on approximately 2.13 acres of land. Property also features an asphalt/concrete parking lot with 53 parking
spaces and 2 ingress/egress points on Pythian.
Current Tenant will vacate the space on 5/31/2020
Please feel free to contact Jeff Childs today for more information or to schedule a showing!

spaceSummary:
This building is part of a 7-building facility previously used by General Dynamics to build tank armor.  This facility will be idle as General Dynamic will be completing its final block order by 1Q 2012.

The parcel of land is zoned 16th Section Public School by the State of Mississippi.  The entire facility sits on 465 acres and is being offered for $44,100 per YEAR.  Buildings are designated ISO 9001, ISO 14001, and ISO 18001.

The site features two miles of paved road, a remote-operated gate and security camera system, and has public water and the capability for heavy industrial power.  The entire sites features over 66,000 square feet of covered workspace.

There is also a readily-available temporary workforce pool of non-union workers.  All ten salaried managers, supervisors, and support staff have more than 20 years of experience.

The CRC Indianola Distribution Center is a 350,000 SF warehouse/distribution facility in Sunflower County, Mississippi.  Food Grade storage and distribution space with 25'-30' clear height.  The facility's previous uses include storage, distribution, manufacturing, and packaging.
Area neighbors include Delta Pride Catfish, Super-Valu distribution facility, Dollar General distribution facility. 
Indianola, MS is an ideal location for distribution. Indianola is located at the juncture of two major highways, U.S. Highway 49 (north/south) and U.S. Highway 82 (east/west). It is ideally situated for the transportation of goods, products and services across the Southeastern United States. Indianola is approximately 100 miles north of Jackson and 135 miles south of Memphis.

propOverview:
Former printing building built in the 1930's   open floor plan offices - flex space, underground parking.   Building is a combination of primarily traditional warehouse space, with shop space and office space sprinkled in.  Our little company is reworking the lighting, carpet, paint, key fob access and getting it ready for new tenants.  Freight elevator, underground parking for 37 cars, parking on side of building for 6 cars and 12 cars in rear.  Meeting room and conference room. Key fob access.  Onsite staff.   
Building is empty at the time of this ad, suites are between 6000 and 1500.  We are located 150' from Minneapolis St Paul border on university.   9-12 minute drive to either downtown Minneapolis or downtown St. Paul.  Bike storage room.  bike storage and Shower room, lockers.   Once leased up and fully finished, the resuly vibrant community that encompasses both office and production folks.  I have had success at another building creating  space that employees appreciate, especially the varied mix of operations and people.   Walk to coffee shop.  Across street from light rail stop.  We think we have a better offering than the suburbs or downtown. dedicated hardworking staff.  give us a chance to earn your business.   Stop by anytime   thanks Pete 612 990 0335

propOverview: FOR LEASE: Approximately 1,400 sf of retail / office space located in downtown Gloucester. Property is under new ownership and undergoing renovations. The property has multiple buildings.  Subject unit is on the right side when entering the lot. Located in Harbor Loop, between The Building Center and Coast Guard Station Gloucester, the property offers off-street parking that will be freshly striped upon completion of renovation and handicap accessibility. The space is located on the first floor of a three story building; with additional space available adjacent to the unit and on the second floor. Due to its' prominent location within Gloucester's inner harbor, Harbor Loop is a popular destination for local residents and visitors alike. In addition to the Coast Guard and Building Center, neighbors include Maritime Gloucester, Captain Carlos Restaurant, the Fitz Henry Lane House and the new home of the Cape Ann Chamber of Commerce.  $2,200 / month.  Rent includes central air, heat, electric, water and sewer. Other units available as renovation continues.  Ask broker for details.

propOverview:
This property boasts one of the best locations in one of the nation’s steadiest economies.  Everly Place at 218 Shrewsbury Street in Worcester, Massachusetts, offers employers a customizable office or retail space in a locale currently booming in population and commerce.  The property is nearing completion of total remodeling, with only this space to be leased and customized.  When completed, this space will include amenities such as an independent main entranceway, private foyer and waiting area, separate utilities, private and secure on-site employee parking, a three-season common area rooftop terrace and standalone signage on the front and side of the building.  Employees will enjoy the brief five-minute walk to multiple high-end and casual restaurants such as the 111 Chophouse, Via Italian Ristorante, and Redemption Rock Brewery.  
Relish in the greenery with a walk through the adjacent Cristoforo Colombo Park or the nearby Green Hill Park.  Commuters will have a drive four minutes to the nearest I-290 exit or Union Station, which provides direct access to Boston.  Baseball fanatics can look forward to the WooSox Minor League team relocating to Worcester as they’ve broken ground on their new stadium and are due to open their first game in the city in 2021.

hoodMarket: Canton sits at the junction of the South Shore highways and adjacent to some of Boston’s most affluent suburbs. The Blue Hills Reservation, offering 6,000 acres of hiking trails, is just minutes north, and Rhode Island’s population centers around Providence and Newport are just an hour south. The advantageous location has attracted industrial tenants and warehouse retailers, which have clustered along Route 24 and the Route 1 junction.,Much of the area’s office and industrial stock is smaller and older and rents at significant discounts to Boston proper. Large occupiers include the global headquarters of Dunkin’; retailers including Destination XL and Talbots; and back-office operations for the finance and insurance sectors.,The nearby highways also serve a substantial manufacturing presence in the area, including tech firms, apparel, and food services and distribution. Siemans chose nearby Walpole as the site for its new R&D facility specializing in laboratory diagnostic devices.
propOverview: “Location, Location, Location” isn’t just a cliché when it comes to 225 Turnpike Street- this former vocational school is located in the affluent Norfolk County and is less than 10 minutes to the numerous retail, dining, and personal services destinations on Washington Street. This property already has classrooms, shop/laboratory space, shower facilities, and loading docks in place, but the potential for multiple different businesses is unlimited. Office tenants could easily make use of the customizable expansive spaces and partitioned rooms, athletic-minded businesses can convert these areas into training spaces and the shower facilities are already built-in, industrial tenants already have shop space and workstations built-out that lends well to warehouses or lab facilities and just a 5-minute drive to both I-93 and I-95 makes distribution a breeze, and the space could easily be repurposed for another education facility that provides ease of access and ample parking space. The proximity to I-93 and I-95 benefits any type of tenant whether it is for distribution or accessibility for commuters from the surrounding region. Tenants also enjoy access to dining choices such as Mai Place and 99 Restaurants minutes down Turnpike Street and a short 10-minute drive to the bustling Washington Street provides options such as Neponset Café, Waterfall Bar & Grille, and Takara. The property has access to the strong demographics of the area that can be utilized as a strong labor force, consumer base, or clientele pool. Norfolk County is the 33rd highest-income county in the United States and is the wealthiest county in Massachusetts, and plenty of businesses have taken advantage of Canton’s central location. Dunkin’ Donuts, Computershare’s North American Branch, and the Salvation Army’s Massachusetts Division have all headquartered in the area, and 225 Turnpike Street provides over 14,000 square feet of potential for businesses to capitalize on the space as they see fit.

propOverview:
Walpole Station Business Center, with approximately 265,000 gross square feet, is a mixed-use historic brick and beam mill property comprised of six interconnected multi-story buildings. Uses include office, light industrial, retail and storage.
The property was originally built in 1897 and expanded in 1951 with ongoing various improvements and renovations.
Located near the center of downtown Walpole, MA at the corner of Elm Street (Route 27) and West Street. Other addresses of the complex include 100 Elm Street, 75-85 and 125 West Street. Short walk to all area amenities and immediately adjacent to the MBTA Walpole commuter rail station. Additionally - 344 brand new Class A apartment units will be delivered starting fall 2019 adjacent to the site!

Tenants may choose to use the dedicated shuttle service to and from the Alewife Redline stop, hop off at the Waverley Commuter Rail Station, take the MBTA 554 bus line, or park in one of the many thousands of free parking spaces located at the park.

propOverview: Business bay in meticulously maintained complex. Generous parking in paved, lined, lighted lot.  This bay has an eve height of approximately 22'. It is fully sprinklered, insulated and has a fire/ burglar alarm system. Separately metered for gas, with a central FHA heating and air conditioning system. Two offices on the first floor and a wide open office space on the second floor. This bay has been used historically for a magazine publisher, home staging/ interior designer and, most recently, a specialty fitness facility. Ideal for anyone who needs to maintain an ideal temperature inside the bay and offices, either for people or product. Centrally and conveniently located, Kidd's Hill Road runs from Phinney's Lane to Independence Drive. Close to all major shopping (Home Depot, BJ's, Stop & Shop, Home Goods, Whole Foods, the Cape Cod Mall and more. A quick, direct route to the Mid-Cape Highway, via Attucks Lane and Route 132 (aka Iyannough Road), Exit 6.

propOverview:
Look no further for your next shop space than this downtown Milford location, just 6 minutes off I-495. This former Jean's Catering building been significantly renovated with all new siding, new windows, new furnaces (1/floor), new renovated offices, new bathrooms and more! Plenty of parking and yard space is also available.
Each floor has the ability to be used for many different purposes such as retail shops, commercial office space, and flex industrial space. The 1st floor/Basement space is perfect for a small construction company, contractor, or light manufacturing company with a combined 5,719 SF (note basement space has a pending lease, but is not final). 1st floor is complete with newly renovated turnkey office space consisting of two private offices, one of which is large (~16'x11') and could double as a small conference room or bullpen for multiple cubicles/desks. A spacious lobby area is adjacent to two newly renovated bathrooms. The warehouse/shop area is complete with 3 overhead doors, ample utility capacity (electric/gas as the property used to be used for catering) and a nice open layout.
The building has three stories:
Basement - 2,696 SF (All warehouse/storage - pending lease)
1st - 3,023 SF (office ~800 SF & Warehouse ~2,800SF)
2nd - 2,697 SF (Leased)

When the company ceased operation, the buildings were left vacant.
